<TITLE> Khoka says he owns five homes, six flats </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 6 (bdnews24.com) -- Dhaka city mayor Sadek Hossain Khoka has said he and his family members own five homes and six apartments in the city. A wealth statement, submitted to the Anticorruption Commission Thursday, recorded immovable property worth Tk 2.92 crore in Khoka's name and property worth Tk 3.71 crore in his wife's name. Khoka also recorded Tk 58.48 lakh and Tk 16.4 lakh in the value of property owned by his son and daughter. The mayor's wife owns eight plots, according to the statement. Their movable property include two carsa Lexus and a Toyota. The statement showed that Khoka, his wife and their daughter own 40 bank accounts. The mayor owns two firearms, the statement said. Advocate ASM Qayyum submitted the statement to the graft watchdog on behalf of Khoka and his family. Earlier, Awami League leader Tofail Ahmed turned in his wealth statement to the ACC and mentioned Tk 1.2 core in wealth. The ACC served notices on 12 people on Nov 18, asking them to submit wealth statements. bdn
